Police Inspector G. Adhikari said bulldozers razed over 50 houses in Dharan that were  damaged in Sunday's earthquake that killed over 730 people in India and Nepal.
Over  131 bodies were found in Dharan, most in collapsed houses that had used rain loosened  mud between the bricks.
Helicopters carrying supplies and rescuers flew into the remote regions of Bihar, India  Heavy rains, overflowing rivers, and submerged bridges and roads hampered recovery  attempts.
Nepal, one of the world's poorest countries, has not yet sought foreign aid.
Aftershocks have persisted, and rumors of a new quake panicked residents in Katmandu  and Dharan Tuesday. 
